properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 12:04PM CST until February 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...PRECIPITATION SPREADING NORTHEAST THIS AFTERNOON...

.A Winter Weather Advisory remains in effect until 3 PM for parts
of south central Minnesota. This advisory also remains in effect
until 9 PM for Freeborn, Steele, and Goodhue counties in
Minnesota, and for Pepin and Eau Claire counties in Wisconsin. The
advisory is based on snowfall amounts of one to three inches,
with locally heavier amounts along the Iowa border this
afternoon.

Precipitation will continue to expand across south central, and
parts of east central Minnesota, as well as west central
Wisconsin Minnesota this afternoon.

A mixture of sleet or rain is possible early this afternoon in
south central Minnesota. However, the precipitation should change
over to all snow during the afternoon, with locally heavy along
the Iowa border. The snow will end early this evening.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations 1 to 2 inches.

* WHERE...Pepin and Eau Claire Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
